The paper discusses the development of an analytical performance predictor for DNN accelerators, which involves the intersection of several computer science subfields. The paper's focus on deep neural networks and their hardware acceleration suggests that it could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Robotics (cs.RO) subcategories. However, the paper's emphasis on the design and optimization of hardware architectures for DNN accelerators suggests that it could also fall under the Computer Architecture (cs.AR) or Embedded Systems (cs.ET) subcategories. Finally, the paper's discussion of energy efficiency and performance optimization suggests that it could also fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) subcategory. Overall, cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.ET, and cs.DC are the most likely subcategories for this paper.
